revision.text: Additional help for Pickle can be found at '''[//www.mediawiki.org/wiki/Help:Pickle Help:Pickle on MediaWiki]''', note especially the subpage '''[//www.mediawiki.org/wiki/Help:Pickle/Vagrant Help:Pickle/Vagrant]'''.

A few testcases are provided for manual testing. These test cases are for manual testing of the overall integration. Usually the unit tests should be sufficient, so these tests are only for final verification. == Exceptional test cases == These are the exceptional cases where most of the framework does not apply. The "missing" case is where there are no test module. The "unknown" case is where there are some kind of test module, but the framework can't recognize the output. Both "missing" and "unknown" are conceptually pending, but whether such a category should be created is up to the community using the extension. {| class="wikitable table-data-center" !State !Normal !''Category'' |- !Missing |[[Module:Missing|Missing]]
{{Mediawiki:pickle-test-text-missing}} |''[[:Category:{{Mediawiki:pickle-tracking-category-missing}}‎|{{Mediawiki:pickle-tracking-category-missing}}‎]]'' |- !Unknown |[[Module:Unknown|Unknown]]
{{Mediawiki:pickle-test-text-unknown}} |''[[:Category:{{Mediawiki:pickle-tracking-category-unknown}}‎|{{Mediawiki:pickle-tracking-category-unknown}}‎]]'' |} == Simple test cases == These are simple cases where the framework do apply. The "hard" cases are hardcoded to give a specific output, without using to much of the Lua framework. The "soft" cases use more of the Lua framework, with a higher probability of failure.
